cs.GT, cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NI 

The paper deals with the game theoretic approach to distributed control, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Computer Science - Game Theory). It also involves resource allocation problems, which can be categorized under cs.DC (Computer Science - Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the design of local utilities, which can be considered as a machine learning problem and hence falls under cs.LG (Computer Science - Learning). Additionally, the paper presents two applications related to wireless data caching and vehicle-target assignment, which can be categorized under cs.NI (Computer Science - Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.AI (Computer Science - Artificial Intelligence), respectively.
